#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
rotten-apple — non-destructive Ubuntu lifter onto Xen.

Treats your existing Ubuntu install as middleware: leaves it untouched on disk,
adds a Xen hypervisor + dom0 boot path alongside the bare-metal one, and
makes that path the default. The bare-metal entry stays in GRUB; if the
hypervisor path fails to come up, hold Shift at boot to choose it.

Subcommands
-----------
  detect        Read host state and print a lift-readiness report.
  lift          Install Xen, add hypervisor GRUB entry, set as default.
  verify        Post-boot health check: confirm we are running as Xen dom0.
  unlift        Restore bare-metal default; optionally remove Xen packages.
  finalize      Re-hide the GRUB menu after `--show-grub-menu` first boot.
  status        Show current lift state.
  refresh       Re-pin the Xen GRUB entry as default after a kernel upgrade.

Files touched (all backed up to /var/lib/rotten-apple/backups/<ts>/):
  /etc/default/grub
  /boot/grub/grub.cfg            (regenerated by update-grub; backed up first)

Files created/owned:
  /var/lib/rotten-apple/state.json
  /var/lib/rotten-apple/backups/
  /var/log/rotten-apple/lift-<ts>.log

Run `detect` first. Run `lift` only after reading the report.
"""

